 {"id":"bd-uf3","title":"[Net] Implement Reactor Abstraction for I/O Multiplexing","description":"# Reactor Abstraction

## Overview
Platform-agnostic reactor for I/O event multiplexing with deterministic lab variant.

## Reactor Trait

```rust
/// I/O event reactor
pub trait Reactor: Send + Sync {
    /// Register interest in I/O events
    fn register(&self, source: &impl Source, interest: Interest) -> io::Result<Registration>;

    /// Deregister source
    fn deregister(&self, registration: Registration) -> io::Result<()>;

    /// Poll for events (blocking)
    fn poll(&self, events: &mut Events, timeout: Option<Duration>) -> io::Result<usize>;

    /// Wake the reactor from another thread
    fn wake(&self) -> io::Result<()>;
}

/// I/O source trait
pub trait Source {
    fn raw_fd(&self) -> RawFd;
}

/// Interest flags
pub struct Interest(u8);

impl Interest {
    pub const READABLE: Interest = Interest(0b01);
    pub const WRITABLE: Interest = Interest(0b10);

    pub fn readable() -> Self { Self::READABLE }
    pub fn writable() -> Self { Self::WRITABLE }
    pub fn both() -> Self { Interest(0b11) }
}

/// Event from reactor
pub struct Event {
    pub token: Token,
    pub readable: bool,
    pub writable: bool,
    pub error: bool,
    pub hangup: bool,
}

/// Events buffer
pub struct Events {
    inner: Vec<Event>,
    capacity: usize,
}
```

## Platform Implementations

### Linux (io_uring preferred, epoll fallback)

```rust
#[cfg(target_os = "linux")]
pub struct IoUringReactor {
    ring: io_uring::IoUring,
    waker: eventfd::EventFd,
}

#[cfg(target_os = "linux")]
pub struct EpollReactor {
    epoll_fd: RawFd,
    waker: eventfd::EventFd,
}
```

### macOS (kqueue)

```rust
#[cfg(target_os = "macos")]
pub struct KqueueReactor {
    kqueue_fd: RawFd,
    waker: Pipe,
}
```

### Windows (IOCP)

```rust
#[cfg(target_os = "windows")]
pub struct IocpReactor {
    port: Handle,
}
```

## Lab Reactor (Deterministic)

```rust
pub struct LabReactor {
    /// Virtual sockets and their state
    sockets: HashMap<Token, VirtualSocket>,

    /// Pending events (deterministic order)
    pending: BinaryHeap<TimedEvent>,

    /// Current virtual time
    time: Time,
}

impl LabReactor {
    /// Inject event (for testing)
    pub fn inject_event(&mut self, token: Token, event: Event, delay: Duration);

    /// Inject connection
    pub fn inject_accept(&mut self, listener: Token, stream: VirtualStream);

    /// Inject read data
    pub fn inject_readable(&mut self, token: Token, data: Vec<u8>);

    /// Inject error
    pub fn inject_error(&mut self, token: Token, error: io::Error);
}
```

## Driver Integration

```rust
/// I/O driver runs reactor and dispatches events
pub struct IoDriver {
    reactor: Box<dyn Reactor>,
    registrations: Slab<Waker>,
}

impl IoDriver {
    /// Run one iteration
    pub fn turn(&mut self, timeout: Option<Duration>) -> io::Result<usize> {
        let mut events = Events::with_capacity(1024);
        let n = self.reactor.poll(&mut events, timeout)?;

        for event in events.iter() {
            if let Some(waker) = self.registrations.get(event.token.0) {
                waker.wake_by_ref();
            }
        }

        Ok(n)
    }
}
```

## Cancel-Safety
- Registration cancellation removes interest
- Pending I/O aborted on deregister
- Events not processed if task cancelled

## Testing
- Register/deregister
- Event delivery
- Wake from another thread
- Lab reactor determinism
- Fault injection via lab

